Section 5 (Conclusion), page 25

The most relevant two problems which we propose as the next natural steps to take towards solving the EFX problem are the following:
) the (non-)existence of complete EFX allocations for three agents with general monotone valuations, and
) the (non-)existence of complete EFX allocations for four agents with additive valuations.

